### Security Awareness Training Records (AT-2, AT-4) — Document Examination

**Documents reviewed:** LMS training completion export; training curriculum outline; training knowledge check passing score records.

**Examination findings:**

Training completion export reviewed for all active OpenMRS users. Current completion status matches the ISSO's Task I-2 documentation — [N] current, [N] overdue users in the 10-business-day remediation window. ✓

Training curriculum reviewed. Content covers all six required topic areas documented in the SSP. Knowledge check passing scores (80% minimum) are recorded in the LMS for all completions. ✓

**Finding A-6 (Low):** The training curriculum does not include a module specifically addressing the OpenMRS downtime scenario — what clinical staff should do if they cannot access OpenMRS during a shift. The general security awareness training covers incident reporting and system outage notification, but does not provide the specific guidance that clinical staff need to operate safely during an EHR outage. This gap connects directly to CP-2 (clinical downtime procedures) — the downtime training cannot be fully delivered until the procedures are complete, but the absence of even basic downtime guidance in the current training curriculum is a gap that could be partially addressed now.

*Note:* This finding overlaps with POA&M-CP3-01 (clinical staff downtime training pending CP-2). The assessor is confirming and strengthening the characterization of that POA&M item rather than creating a duplicative finding — the POA&M item should be updated to note that interim basic downtime guidance should be added to the current training curriculum while the full procedure is being developed.

