### Contingency Plan (CP-2, CP-4) — Document Examination

**Documents reviewed:** MyClinic OpenMRS Contingency Plan (technical recovery section; clinical downtime procedures draft); quarterly restoration test records.

**Examination findings:**

Technical recovery procedures reviewed. Step-by-step instructions are clear and specific. The procedure includes a verification checklist confirming that the restored system is functional before clinical use resumes. The most recent quarterly restoration test record shows completion within the 4-hour RTO with data integrity verified. ✓

Clinical downtime procedures draft reviewed. The draft covers patient registration in paper mode and basic encounter documentation. It does not address: medication management during downtime, laboratory result handling for results that arrive during downtime, or care plan continuity for patients with complex chronic conditions. The draft has been reviewed with one clinical staff member for feedback but has not been formally reviewed by the clinical leadership team.

The assessor's assessment of the CP-2 POA&M characterization: the POA&M describes clinical downtime procedures as "partially implemented — draft exists, not tested." The assessor finds this characterization accurate. The draft scope is more limited than described in the POA&M — "draft exists" implies a substantially complete draft awaiting testing; the actual draft covers two of approximately five functional areas. The assessor will note in the SAR that the CP-2 POA&M item may require a revised target date and expanded scope description.

